# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SUPABASE — Postgres connection (transaction pooler)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Where to find these:
#   Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → Database → Connection string → URI
#
# Both URLs use the same host/user/password — only roles differ:
#   DATABASE_URL = runtime queries (used by the Next.js app)
#   DIRECT_URL   = migrations / schema pushes
#
# Notes:
# - Replace [YOUR-PASSWORD] with your real Supabase database password.
# - Use a password with letters and numbers ONLY (no symbols like ! @ # $).
#   The pooler is fussy about URL-encoded passwords and avoiding symbols
#   sidesteps the issue.
# - The hostname Supabase shows in the dashboard CAN be wrong for new
#   projects (it sometimes defaults to aws-0-us-east-1 even when the
#   project actually lives in a different region/cluster). If you get
#   "FATAL: Tenant or user not found" with the dashboard's URL, try
#   probing alternate prefixes: aws-0-…, aws-1-…, and common regions
#   (us-east-1, us-east-2, us-west-1, us-west-2, eu-central-1, …).
# - The legacy direct host (db.PROJECTREF.supabase.co:5432) is IPv6-only
#   on the free tier — not reachable from most ISPs. Always use the
#   pooler instead.

DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres.YOUR-PROJECT-REF:[YOUR-PASSWORD]@aws-1-us-west-2.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?pgbouncer=true&connection_limit=1"
DIRECT_URL="postgresql://postgres.YOUR-PROJECT-REF:[YOUR-PASSWORD]@aws-1-us-west-2.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?pgbouncer=true"

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ADMIN
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Used to gate the /admin dashboard. Set to a long random string in prod.
ADMIN_PASSWORD="set-a-strong-password"
